# JavaScript Function Basics

## Function Declaration

```javascript
// Function declaration
function sum(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Function call
console.log(sum(3, 4)); // Outputs: 7
```

### Function Declaration Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B{Input}
    B -->|Valid| C[Execute Function]
    B -->|Invalid| D[Return Error]
    C --> E[Output Result]
    D --> E
    E --> F[End]
```

# Function Expressions

## Example of Function Expression

```javascript
// Assigning a function expression to a variable
const multiply = function(x, y) {
    return x * y;
};

// Function call
console.log(multiply(5, 6)); // Outputs: 30
```

### Execution Flow:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant JS
    User->>JS: multiply(5, 6)
    JS-->>User: 30
```

# JavaScript Closures

## Understanding Closures

```javascript
function makeCounter() {
    let count = 0;
    return function() {
        count += 1;
        return count;
    };
}

const counter = makeCounter();
console.log(counter()); // Outputs: 1
console.log(counter()); // Outputs: 2
```

### Closure Diagram:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[makeCounter] --> B((count))
    B --> C[Inner Function]
    C --> D[Return Updated Count]
```
